It's fun, but it's *very* challenging.  You'll burn a lot of time getting through missions.  Eats some battery, sure, but no more than expected with such a graphics-heavy game.  Gameplay is *excellent*, well above par, graphics are great, animations are great.  It's well worth the price tag.  Try the demo first, because this game isn't for everyone.

ARMA Tactics is a rather mediocre tactical puzzler that lacks variety and movement options, has dumb AI, odd pathfinding glitches, dubious Line-of-Sight and cover, map clutter that obfuscates positions, unfinishably buggy random missions and a slew of smaller problems. Not what I'd have expected from Bohemia, even its cheapness doesn't save it: a proper game at a proper price is always better than something that's haphazardly thrown together in order to try and cash in on the TBS horse the new XCOM got rolling. This isn't anywhere near as good as that, and I'm thinking I'd rather play golden oldies on an emulator than recommend this to anyone. =/

A good and realistic game! Beginners may find it difficult because enemies are almost as skillful as your soldiers. Once a man is down, you lose the game. Soldiers have to take good cover to protect themselves. Bullets can penetrate light covers such as a thin wall, so don't stay too close to the wall.  However, it is not perfect yet: 1. The instructions in the tutorial mission is not sufficient to thoroughly familiarize new players of the interface. It took me a while to understand how it works. 2. The font is a bit too small. It's hard to read on my phone. 3. Check-points or "Save" should be given to allow the players to start-over more conveniently.

It does not crash on my device (Galaxy Note 10.1), sometimes a bit laggy, but it is not a big deal.  I had a lot of fun and decent challenges during a gameplay. I really enjoyed it.  Some tips to play: - it is a tactical game, no crazy-shooting game, positioning makes a difference. - buy a sniper rifle (you can have 95% shots, 90% from a distance without enemy seeing you) - never keep your soldier alone - check each corner first, if you run somewhere and get intercepted, you did a serious mistake - don't attack an enemy with one soldier, it is too risky - use grenades on enemies hidden behind obstacles  - I don't even attack with a knife from back if I have only one try. It is better to wait a turn, because even a knife attack may fail

content: If you like turn based strategy, there aren't many better on android.   The graphics are great and the action cam is a nice touch.  Arma fan.  The devs Bohemia are super involved if you're an Arma or DayZ fan.

Although, a great addition would be the ability to replay mission's in full speed after completing it in the after action report. I think we'd all agree it'd be cool to go back and watch your whole mission in full speed, especially when you did pretty badass.
All lovers of strategy, download this!
It actually made my phone resrart at the end of bootcamp. Demo worked fine. Can I get a refund,please? I have a droid incredible,by the way.

If you have a pc try full spectrum warrior, way better game.  This is glitchy, throwing a grenade at an opponent over a wall generally results in your own death. Keep your squad tightly grouped, maximise firepower. Not so much chess as brute force and camping wins. Wait for the enemy to come to you, buy rifle upgrades asap.  Decent for the platform but frustrating to start with, try the demo first.
